<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Among reef rubble, in particular under dead fungiid coral skeletons, in shallow coral reef areas. Depth 4-8 m</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonomo &amp; Gosliner" authorityYear="2020" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Chromodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chromodoris balat" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balat">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chromodoris balat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the Philippines (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" author="Bonomo, L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="401 - 435" refId="B28" refString="Bonomo, L, Gosliner, TM, 2020. Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species. Zootaxa 4819: 401 - 435, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" title="Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" volume="4819" year="2020">Bonomo and Gosliner 2020</bibRefCitation>
) and a similar species is recorded here for the first time from Thai waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="73" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="73">
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonomo &amp; Gosliner" authorityYear="2020" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Chromodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chromodoris balat" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balat">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chromodoris balat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a striated dorsum with numerous large blotches and a broken yellow-orange marginal line. This species was differentiated from the similar 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergh" authorityYear="1877" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Chromodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chromodoris striatella" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chromodoris striatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bergh, 1877 based on these and other features (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" author="Layton, K" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="27 - 36" refId="B144" refString="Layton, K, Gosliner, T, Wilson, N, 2018. Flexible colour patterns obscure identification and mimicry in Indo-Pacific Chromodoris nudibranchs (Gastropoda: Chromodorididae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 124: 27 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" title="Flexible colour patterns obscure identification and mimicry in Indo-Pacific Chromodoris nudibranchs (Gastropoda: Chromodorididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" volume="124" year="2018">Layton et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" author="Bonomo, L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="401 - 435" refId="B28" refString="Bonomo, L, Gosliner, TM, 2020. Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species. Zootaxa 4819: 401 - 435, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" title="Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" volume="4819" year="2020">Bonomo and Gosliner 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Our specimen is differentiated from 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. balat" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balat">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">C. balat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by lacking small yellow, orange, and red spots on the white parts of the dorsal surface, the pale tan-coloured gills with orange spots instead of red-brown as seen in 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. balat" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balat">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">C. balat</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and by the blotches being pale grey-brown and indistinct instead of dark and pronounced. The indistinct blotches on the dorsum, the broken yellow-orange marginal band, and the colouration of rhinophores and gills do share a resemblance with 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. mandapamensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mandapamensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">C. mandapamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. mandapamensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mandapamensis">C. cf. mandapamensis</taxonomicName>
(the latter of which may be found living alongside 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. balat" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="balat">C. cf. balat</taxonomicName>
at Koh Tao). Given the difficulties of relying on external features for species delineation in many of these striped and spotted species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alder &amp; Hancock" authorityYear="1855" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Chromodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chromodoris" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chromodoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" author="Layton, K" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="27 - 36" refId="B144" refString="Layton, K, Gosliner, T, Wilson, N, 2018. Flexible colour patterns obscure identification and mimicry in Indo-Pacific Chromodoris nudibranchs (Gastropoda: Chromodorididae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 124: 27 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" title="Flexible colour patterns obscure identification and mimicry in Indo-Pacific Chromodoris nudibranchs (Gastropoda: Chromodorididae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2018.02.008" volume="124" year="2018">Layton et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" author="Bonomo, L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="401 - 435" refId="B28" refString="Bonomo, L, Gosliner, TM, 2020. Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species. Zootaxa 4819: 401 - 435, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" title="Adding stars to the Chromodoris (Nudibranchia, Chromodorididae) galaxy with the description of four new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4819.3.1" volume="4819" year="2020">Bonomo and Gosliner 2020</bibRefCitation>
) we refrain from committing to a species identification until specimens from Koh Tao can be investigated further. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" author="Chavanich, S" journalOrPublisher="Marine Biodiversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" pagination="31 - 36" refId="B49" refString="Chavanich, S, Viyakarn, V, Sanpanich, K, Harris, L, 2013. Diversity and occurrence of nudibranchs in Thailand. Marine Biodiversity 43: 31 - 36, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" title="Diversity and occurrence of nudibranchs in Thailand." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s12526-012-0141-4" volume="43" year="2013">Chavanich et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. striatella" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">C. striatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from both Gulf and Andaman coasts of Thailand; however, in the absence of specimen details from both areas, this distribution record may be called into question in light of the recent findings regarding the complex surrounding 
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. striatella" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">C. striatella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further documentation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alder &amp; Hancock" authorityYear="1855" class="Gastropoda" family="Chromodorididae" genus="Chromodoris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chromodoris" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="0" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="73">Chromodoris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species from both coasts may clarify this.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
